    "name": "Online Edition of Jacob Bernoulli's Reisebüchlein",
    "shortDescription": "RDF-star-based digital edition of Jacob Bernoulli's travel journal (1676-1683), with facsimiles, transcriptions, and dynamic journey visualizations.",
    "description": {
        "en": "Jacob Bernoulli (1654-1705) embarked on extensive travels spanning seven years (1676-1683) across Switzerland, France, the Netherlands, Belgium, Germany, and England. The Reisebüchlein (little travel book) is a small-format autograph document of 195 pages preserved at the Universitätsbibliothek Basel (UBH L Ia 5). This digital edition project generates an RDF-star-based edition of the travel journal, presenting it as a region-based, multilayered, interactive digital edition with facsimiles, transcriptions, and dynamic visualizations of journeys on the Bernoulli Euler Digital platform."
    },
